tients who need ongoing cardiac monitoring and safety clearance to participate safely in intensive robotic and physical rehabilitation programs.","At Ayurgreen Hospital, we understand that a recovering stroke or TBI patient cannot achieve their full rehabilitation potential if their heart health is not simultaneously optimized. Our cardiologists are an integral part of the multidisciplinary team, ensuring that every patient's recovery is both safe and maximally effective."],"image":"Assets/rehab/prog_stroke.webp","imageAlt":"Cardiology at Ayurgreen Hospital"},"conditions":{"sectionLabel":"CONDITIONS WE MANAGE","sectionTitle":"Cardiac Conditions We Specialize In","sectionSupport":"Expert cardiac management for both general patients and the complex cardiovascular needs of our neurological rehabilitation population.","cards":[{"image":"Assets/rehab/prog_stroke.webp","title":"Coronary & Hypertensive Disease","description":"Ischemic heart disease, acute coronary syndrome, hypertensive heart disease, and heart failure management. The cornerstone of stroke prevention — vital for our neurological rehabilitation patients."},{"image":"Assets/rehab/prog_spinal_cord.webp","title":"Arrhythmias & Rhythm Disorders","description":"Atrial fibrillation (AF) — the most common cause of cardioembolic stroke — along with other supraventricular and ventricular arrhythmias. Expert ECG, Holter, and echocardiographic evaluation for precise diagnosis and management."},{"image":"Assets/rehab/prog_parkinsons.webp","title":"Cardiac Rehabilitation","description":"Structured exercise-based cardiac rehabilitation programs for post-MI, post-cardiac surgery, and heart failure patients. Integrated with our physiotherapy team for safe, supervised progressive exercise."}]},"treatments":{"sectionLabel":"CARDIAC SERVICES","sectionTitle":"Comprehensive Cardiac Care","sectionSupport":"Expert cardiac diagnostics, medical management, and rehabilitation — integrated into our neurological recovery ecosystem.","steps":[{"image":"Assets/rehab/prog_stroke.webp","title":"Cardiac Assessment for Rehabilitation Clearance","description":"Before intensive rehabilitation begins, all patients with cardiac risk factors undergo comprehensive cardiac evaluation by our cardiologists. Echocardiography, stress testing, and Holter monitoring ensure that every patient is safe to begin high-intensity robotic and physiotherapy sessions — preventing cardiac events during recovery."},{"image":"Assets/rehab/th_physiotherapy.webp","title":"Exercise-Based Cardiac Rehabilitation","description":"Our cardiologists work alongside physiotherapists to design safe, progressive exercise programs for cardiac rehabilitation patients. Continuous cardiac monitoring during exercise sessions ensures safety while building cardiovascular fitness, improving heart function, and reducing future cardiac risk."},{"image":"Assets/rehab/th_panchakarma.webp","title":"Ayurvedic Cardioprotective Therapies","description":"Authentic Ayurvedic cardioprotective therapies including Hridya (cardiac) rasayanas like Arjuna (Terminalia arjuna) formulations, proven to improve cardiac muscle function and reduce arrhythmias. Stress-reducing Ayurvedic therapies like Shirodhara and yoga are integrated as part of a holistic cardiac wellness program."},{"image":"Assets/rehab/th_robotic.webp","title":"Stroke Prevention Cardiology","description":"Specialized cardiology services focused on secondary stroke prevention for our neurological rehabilitation patients. Optimal anticoagulation management for atrial fibrillation, lipid management for atherosclerosis, and blood pressure control — the most critical interventions to prevent a second stroke."}]},"technologies":{"sectionLabel":"CARDIAC DIAGNOSTICS","sectionTitle":"Advanced Cardiac Technology","sectionSupport":"Comprehensive cardiac diagnostic capabilities to accurately assess and monitor cardiovascular health.","cards":[{"icon":"heart","title":"Echocardiography","description":"2D and Doppler echocardiography for detailed assessment of cardiac structure and function — essential for evaluating the heart as a source of stroke emboli."},{"icon":"activity","title":"ECG & Holter Monitoring","description":"12-lead ECG for acute cardiac assessment and 24/48-hour Holter monitoring to detect paroxysmal atrial fibrillation — the most common preventable cause of stroke."},{"icon":"trending-up","title":"Stress Testing (TMT)","description":"Treadmill stress testing to evaluate exercise tolerance and detect significant coronary artery disease, critical for cardiac clearance before rehabilitation begins."},{"icon":"leaf","title":"Ayurvedic Cardio Tonics","description":"Evidence-based Ayurvedic cardiac formulations (Arjuna, Pushkarmool) that support heart muscle strength, improve cardiac efficiency, and manage mild-to-moderate hypertension naturally."},{"icon":"shield-plus","title":"Cardiac Safety Monitoring","description":"Continuous cardiac telemetry monitoring for high-risk rehabilitation patients, ensuring immediate detection and response to any cardiac events during intensive therapy sessions."}]},"faq":{"sectionSupport":"Find answers to key details about the Cardiology program.","items":[{"question":"What is the recovery protocol for this program?","answer":"Our recovery protocol for Cardiology combines daily intensive rehabilitation therapies (robotic support and physical therapy) with personalized Ayurvedic nerve nourishment and systemic detoxification to accelerate functional gains."},{"question":"How long is the typical inpatient stay?","answer":"Most inpatient stays range from 14 to 28 days. A comprehensive assessment is conducted on arrival to map specific milestones, timelines, and discharge pathways."},{"question":"Is robotic therapy safe for all patients?","answer":"Yes, robotic training is safe and is adjusted based on muscle strength, joint ranges, and fatigue levels. Every session is directly supervised by certified clinical engineers and therapists."},{"question":"Are the Ayurvedic medicines safe?","answer":"All herbal oils and medicines are sourced from GMP-certified traditional pharmacies and undergo rigorous testing. They are prescribed specifically to match the patient's biological state."},{"question":"Can we coordinate with our existing neurologist?","answer":"Absolutely. We encourage multidisciplinary alignment and coordinate closely with the patient's referring clinicians to ensure continuity of care."},{"question":"What is the daily therapy schedule?","answer":"A typical day includes active physical and robotic rehabilitation in the morning, followed by relaxing Ayurvedic therapies and counseling sessions in the afternoon."},{"question":"Do you offer post-discharge support?","answer":"Yes, we provide detailed home-exercise regimens, custom orthotic consultations, and online follow-ups to ensure patients maintain their functional gains."},{"question":"How do I book a consultation?","answer":"You can book a virtual consultation by submitting your medical records online, messaging our coordinators via WhatsApp, or calling our helpline directly."}]}}}]],[["$","link","0",{"rel":"stylesheet","href":"/_next/static/css/6e9fffbbd38092f6.css","precedence":"next","crossOrigin":"$undefined","nonce":"$undefined"}]],["$","$La",null,{"children":"$Lb"}]]}],{},null,false]},null,false]},null,false],["$","$1","h",{"children":[null,["$","$1","K-dicVL-1fCdKYitcE3n3",{"children":[["$","$Lc",null,{"children":"$Ld"}],["$","$Le",null,{"children":"$Lf"}],null]}]]}],false]],"m":"$undefined","G":["$10","$undefined"],"s":false,"S":true}
